article.headline: Sam Houston St. 77, Arkansas State 74
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas (AP) -- Joe Thompson scored 21 points to lead Sam Houston State to a 77-74 victory over Arkansas State Monday night. Thompson hit 5-of-11 from 3-point range for the Bearkats (5-5). Eddy Fobbs added 16 points and Chris Jordan and Ryan Bright each scored 10 points for Sam Houston State. Dewarick Spencer and J.J. Montgomery each scored 19 points to lead Arkansas State (5-3). Montgomery also had 11 rebounds. Kitus Witherspoon also had 11 rebounds for the Indians. Sam Houston State led 32-29 at the half. The Bearkats led by 15 at 70-55 with 4:53 left and withstood a late rally by Arkansas State.
